abstract: JPMorgan Chase, the world’s second-biggest custodian of assets, agreed to buy 200 billion euros, or $315.6 billion, of investments from Nordea Bank, the Nordic region’s biggest bank by value.
lead_paragraph: JPMorgan Chase, the world’s second-biggest custodian of assets, agreed to buy 200 billion euros, or $315.6 billion, of investments from Nordea Bank, the Nordic region’s biggest bank by value.
